docs.abstract: Several companies are developing sustainable, plant-based or laboratory-made seafood alternatives. It might help the planet, but will anyone eat it?
docs.snippet: Several companies are developing sustainable, plant-based or laboratory-made seafood alternatives. It might help the planet, but will anyone eat it?
docs.lead_paragraph: First, there was the meatless burger. Soon we may have fishless fish.

headline.print_headline: Today’s Catch: Fresh From the Lab

docs.abstract: R. J. Scaringe’s company, Rivian, has raised $1.7 billion from Amazon, Ford Motor and others without selling a single pickup truck and sport utility vehicle.
docs.snippet: R. J. Scaringe’s company, Rivian, has raised $1.7 billion from Amazon, Ford Motor and others without selling a single pickup truck and sport utility vehicle.
docs.lead_paragraph: NORMAL, Ill. — By definition, the time of the world’s richest man is pretty valuable. But early last fall, Jeff Bezos sought out a 36-year old entrepreneur named R.J. Scaringe and spent the better part of a day in Plymouth, Mich., at the company he founded, Rivian.

headline.main: Meet the Man Quietly Building the Tesla of Trucks, With Jeff Bezos Aboard
headline.print_headline: Think Tesla, but with trucks and S.U.V.s instead of cars.

keywords.value: Sports Utility Vehicles and Light Trucks

docs.abstract: For sitcoms, dramas and reality shows, the jump to streaming was easy. But talk shows? It’s tricky.
docs.snippet: For sitcoms, dramas and reality shows, the jump to streaming was easy. But talk shows? It’s tricky.
docs.lead_paragraph: Netflix upended the entertainment business by successfully moving into nearly every genre — scripted dramas, comedies, stand-up specials, documentaries, reality shows and feature films. But one type of programming has proved tricky for the streaming giant: the talk show.

headline.main: Netflix Has a Talk Show Problem
headline.print_headline: Netflix’s Conquest of TV Hits Obstacle: Talk Shows

docs.abstract: A report by Federal Reserve officials said that United States economic activity increased at a “solid pace” in early 2019, but that risks still loomed.
docs.snippet: A report by Federal Reserve officials said that United States economic activity increased at a “solid pace” in early 2019, but that risks still loomed.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Federal Reserve officials worry that the uncertainty caused by the trade war between the United States and China could be constraining business spending and may be contributing to a manufacturing slowdown that is dragging on growth.

headline.main: Trade War May Be Slowing Business Spending and Factories, Fed Says
headline.print_headline: Trade War May Be Causing Businesses to Delay Spending, Fed Says

docs.abstract: The departure of Garth Ritchie, head of the investment bank, is likely a first step in a broad bid by the bank to reverse its decline.
docs.snippet: The departure of Garth Ritchie, head of the investment bank, is likely a first step in a broad bid by the bank to reverse its decline.
docs.lead_paragraph: FRANKFURT — Deutsche Bank said on Friday that the leader of its investment banking unit would resign, foreshadowing what are likely to be steep cuts in the bank’s operations in the United States and Europe.

headline.main: Deutsche Bank Executive to Leave in Sign of Steep Cuts Ahead
headline.print_headline: Deutsche Bank Executive to Make Ominous Exit

docs.abstract: Before the cult of the modern corporate chief, the former Chrysler leader fused his identity with his company’s, helping him sell cars and win over Washington.
docs.snippet: Before the cult of the modern corporate chief, the former Chrysler leader fused his identity with his company’s, helping him sell cars and win over Washington.
docs.lead_paragraph: Long before Lee Iacocca ran the Ford Motor Company and then the Chrysler Corporation, there were corporate leaders who captured the public’s imagination, like John D. Rockefeller, Walt Disney, Estée Lauder and Henry Ford.

headline.main: Lee Iacocca Was a C.E.O. for the Television Age

docs.abstract: A British regulator ordered that an Amazon-led cash infusion into the food-delivery start-up be paused to study whether it creates competition concerns.
docs.snippet: A British regulator ordered that an Amazon-led cash infusion into the food-delivery start-up be paused to study whether it creates competition concerns.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — Britain’s competition regulator said on Friday that it had begun an investigation into a $575 million investment led by Amazon in the London-based food-delivery service Deliveroo, the latest effort by a government to potentially check the reach of a technology giant.

headline.main: Amazon’s Deliveroo Investment Is Halted for U.K. Scrutiny
headline.print_headline: British Inquiry Stalls Amazon’s Investment In Food Delivery Service

docs.abstract: The purpose of this column has been to show how we can learn from those who have had financial success (or bigger flops) to improve our own financial lives.
docs.snippet: The purpose of this column has been to show how we can learn from those who have had financial success (or bigger flops) to improve our own financial lives.
docs.lead_paragraph: When my first Wealth Matters column ran in December 2008, I wrote that I wanted to examine the strategies the wealthy used to manage their money and their lives in a way that people with far less money could learn from.

headline.main: At Column No. 500, a Look Back at Lessons Learned
headline.print_headline: Taxes, Tigers and Trust Funds, Oh My!

docs.abstract: More U.S. retirees are moving away, and they are finding that Medicare doesn’t pay for health care outside the country. The solution: Mixing coverages.
docs.snippet: More U.S. retirees are moving away, and they are finding that Medicare doesn’t pay for health care outside the country. The solution: Mixing coverages.
docs.lead_paragraph: When Karen Schirack, 67, slipped on her way into her house in January and broke her left femur in multiple places, she had a decision to make. Should she get surgery to repair the fractured thigh bone and replace her hip near Ajijic, Mexico, where she has lived for 20 years, or be airlifted back to her home state, Ohio, for surgery and rehabilitation?

headline.main: Dream of Retiring Abroad? The Reality: Medicare Doesn’t Travel Well

docs.abstract: The studio’s upcoming slate includes the first openly L.G.B.T.Q. superhero in a Marvel film, a superhero who is disabled, and a film anchored by an Asian superhero.
docs.snippet: The studio’s upcoming slate includes the first openly L.G.B.T.Q. superhero in a Marvel film, a superhero who is disabled, and a film anchored by an Asian superhero.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Marvel Studios has generated more than $22 billion in global ticket sales since 2008. Its 23 movies during that period have turned minor comic-book characters like Iron Man and Rocket Raccoon into cultural touchstones. Even “Ant-Man” was a hit.

headline.main: Marvel Studios Unveils Diverse Film Lineup at Comic-Con
headline.print_headline: What’s Next at Marvel? A Diverse Film Lineup and Disney Plus
